Key Match Events: Yves Bissouma salvaged a point for Mali with a goal after his side had fallen behind to a Geny Catamo strike.
Pre-Game Insights: Eswatini come into this game on the back of a 1-0 defeat away to Guinea-Bissau in their first AFCON qualifier.
Eswatini's new head coach Zdravko Logarusic replaced Dominic Kunene in August.
Mali's new head coach Tom Saintfiet replaced Eric Chelle in August.
Mali are considered favourites to top Group I for the AFCON qualifiers.
